A: The problem is in this line:
indexList.add(collectionData.toString().indexOf(searchName.get(i).toString()));

You are converting the entire collectionData array to a string and then calling indexOf on that string. This means that you are actually searching for the entire array as a string, not for individual elements of the array.
Instead, you should call indexOf on individual elements of the array. Here is the corrected code:
for (int j = 0; j < collectionData.length; j++) {
    indexList.add(Arrays.asList(collectionData).indexOf(searchName.get(i)));
    break;
}

This will correctly find the index of each element in the collectionData array.

